# bjw-s app-template Chart

Used for deploying single-image applications via ArgoCD on OpenShift.

## Chart Source
- Chart: `app-template`
- Repo: `https://bjw-s-labs.github.io/helm-charts`
- Version: `4.2.0`

## Values Structure

```yaml
controllers:
  main:
    strategy: RollingUpdate
    labels:
      app.openshift.io/runtime: nodejs  # OpenShift console icon
    annotations:
      openshift.io/required-scc: anyuid  # if the image needs root/anyuid
    serviceAccount:
      name: <sa-name>
    containers:
      main:
        image:
          repository: ghcr.io/org/image
          tag: v1.0.0
          pullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        env:
          - name: KEY
            value: val
          - name: SECRET_KEY
            valueFrom:
              secretKeyRef:
                name: my-secret
                key: secret-key

defaultPodOptions:          # only if needed (e.g. run as root)
  securityContext:
    runAsUser: 0
    runAsGroup: 0

serviceAccount:
  default:
    enabled: true
    labels:
      name: <sa-name>

service:
  main:
    controller: main
    ports:
      http:
        port: 8080

ingress:
  main:
    annotations:
      route.openshift.io/termination: "edge"  # creates an OpenShift Route
    hosts:
      - host: myapp.apps.ocp.kounex.com
        paths:
          - path: /
            pathType: Prefix
            service:
              identifier: main
              port: http

persistence:                # optional
  data:
    storageClass: lvms-vg1
    accessMode: ReadWriteOnce
    size: 5Gi
    globalMounts:
      - path: /data

configMaps:                 # optional
  config:
    enabled: true
    data:
      key: value
```

## Canonical Examples
- Frontend (no persistence, env vars): `manifests/apps/bracket/apps/application-frontend.yml`
- Backend (with PVC, secretKeyRef, SCC): `manifests/apps/bracket/apps/application-backend.yml`

## OpenShift Notes
- `ingress` with `route.openshift.io/termination: "edge"` creates an OpenShift Route automatically
- Images needing root require SCC annotation and a matching RoleBinding to `anyuid`
- `app.openshift.io/runtime` label controls the icon in the OpenShift console topology view
